body.description: Similac Sensitive* is an easy-to-digest, milk-based infant formula designed for sensitive tummies. It’s complete nutrition for fussiness,† gas,† or mild spit-up. Our formula has our exclusive blend of nutrients to help support baby’s brain and eye development. Similac was the first leading infant formula brand with no artificial growth hormones‡ and is the #1 infant formula brand fed in hospitals. * Not for infants or children with galactosemia. † Due to lactose sensitivity. ‡ No significant difference has been shown between milk derived from rbST-treated and non-rbST-treated cows.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: First and Only Formulas with 2’-FL HMO Similac Pro-Advance and Pro-Sensitive include 2’-FL Human Milk Oligosaccharide, an immune-nourishing prebiotic previously only found in breast milk.* 2’-FL is backed by more than 15 years of extensive research. Similac with 2’-FL HMO helps strengthen baby’s immune system to be more like a breastfed infant than ever before. Both formulas are also non-GMO† with the nourishment you’ve come to expect from Similac. *At significant levels. †Ingredients not genetically engineered. Exclusive Blend of Nutrients Optigro is our exclusive blend of DHA, Lutein, and Vitamin E, which are important ingredients found in breast milk. DHA supports brain development, Lutein supports eye health, and Vitamin E is an important nutrient found in breast milk that supports developing cells. Welcome to Toddlerhood Go & Grow by Similac provides important nutrients that may be low in your toddler’s diet as you begin to introduce table food. Whether you’re mixing Go & Grow by Similac Mix-ins into their food or using Go & Grow by Similac Toddler Drink to complement their diet, we have options to help support your child’s growth and development.

reviews.reviewText: My granddaughter stomach was very sensitive so this was the best product for her and helped her a lot with her digestive system thanks for that product

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2011
reviews.reviewText: Good price for product... i had started my baby on the similac soy formula but it was too much for my son's tummy... this formula was a welcomed change.... unfortunately, it came at the funky time of similac's big recall of all the larger containers (i was buying the 34oz can from the wholesale store) and the smaller containers were all sold out of the local stores... not a fun situation... finding this 6-pack at a reasonable price was a much needed and appreciated rescue!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 13, 2014
reviews.reviewText: We use similac sensitive, i usually buy the big carton of this but I like having extras around. Especially if i needed to send one to grandma's house or take with me when traveling.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reduced spit-up and a happier baby!
reviews.reviewText: This formula is a life-saver! Our 2-month old had a little viral bug, which made him spit up a lot and be very fussy. With this formula, he barely spits up at all and has been so much happier!Ask your doctor for a sample! When we took our baby in for his tummy troubles, the doc gave us a full-sized can of this formula to take home and try! Considering it costs about $14 retail, this was great!Pros:Reduced spit-up and gasReduced fussinessEasy to mix upCons:Baby can't go as long between feedings, probably because it's easier to digestYou can also get 2 free cans of Similac (one Advance and one Sensitive) by mail if you register at their website. Great product and great customer service!
